MEIKICHI NISHIMURA, Appellant, v. John D. NAGLE, as Commissioner of Immigration, Port of San Francisco, California, Appellee. No. 6701. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. April 6, 1932. George R. Anderson, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Geo. J. Hatfield, U. S. Atty., of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellant, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate in 30 days.
